This code will produce the two automata as shown in the image. The first automaton on the left represents the two primitive \( b \)-cycles with the associated words \( 0011 \) and \( 001 \). The second automaton on the right represents the \( b \)-cycle of \( \{0, \alpha\} \) with the associated word \( 0011 \odot 001 = 001101111011 \), which is primitive by Lemma~\ref{lm:primitive product}.

